{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> ἀφηγ-έομαι</b>, <br /> <i>Ionic dialect</i> ἀπηγ-, <b>lead the way from</b> a point, and so generally, <b>lead the way, go first,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Leges” 760d, etc.; οἱ ἀφηγούμενοι \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>the van,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 4.8.37\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἀ. τῆς ἀποικίας, τῆς ἀγέλης, <b>to be leader of</b>.., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Aristoteles Philosophus “Fragmenta” 514, “Mir.” 831a22; πρεσβείας 1st c.BC-1st c.AD: Strabo Geographus 1.3.1; τῆς σχολῆς 3rd c.AD(?): Diogenes Laertius 4.14; τῆς Ἀκαδημείας 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “Academicorum Index” p.57 M.; ζῴων 3rd c.AD: Porphyrius Tyrius Philosophus “de Abstinentia - Porphyrii Opuscula” 2.38\">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; οὐκ ἀφηγησαμένῳ δὴ τὸ τέλος ἐγένετο died without ever <b>taking up his command,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 1st c.BC: Philodemus Philosophus “Academicorum Index” p.61M. \">Refs 1st c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <b>tell, relate,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 1.24, +others, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Supplices” 186\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>assert,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD: Aretaeus Medicus “ὀξέων νούσων θεραπευτικόν” 2.7\">Refs 2nd c.AD+</a>]:—<i>perfect</i> in <i>passive</i> sense, ἀπήγηταί μοί τι[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 5.62; τὸ ἀπηγημένον \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<b>what has been told,</b> [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" [prev. author] 1.207, compare 9.26.\">Refs</a>]","strongNumber":"G6622","accentedUnicode":"ἀφηγέομαι","shortDef":"to guide","mediumDef":"to guide","stepGloss":"to guide","stepTransliteration":"afēgeomai","count":0,"_step_Type":"verb"}]}